== Shrines Dedicated to Seoritsu-hime == Significant shrines dedicated to Seoritsu-hime include: - {{ill|Hayachine Shrine|ja|早池峰神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Iwate Prefecture) - {{ill|Taki Shrine|ja|瀧澤神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Miyagi Prefecture) - {{ill|Unojiro Wake Shrine|ja|宇奈己呂和気神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Fukushima Prefecture) - {{ill|Hibiya Shrine|ja|日比谷神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Tokyo) - {{ill|Kifune Shrine|ja|貴船神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Kyoto) - {{ill|Rokkohime Shrine|ja|六甲比命神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Hyōgo Prefecture)
Shrines linking Seoritsu-hime with Amaterasu’s Aramitama include: - {{ill|Aramatsuri-no-Miya|ja|荒祭宮|fr|Aramatsuri_no_miya|es|Aramatsuri no miya|12=draft|12=draft}} (Mie Prefecture) - {{ill|Hirota Shrine|ja|廣田神社|12=draft|12=draft}} (Hyōgo Prefecture) - {{ill|Yamaguchi Grand Shrine|ja|山口大神宮|12=draft|12=draft}} (Yamaguchi Prefecture)
== Other Information == As of October 27, 2015, "Seoritsu-hime" was registered as a trademark by a private company. The registration encompasses an unusually broad range of 43 categories, marking an unprecedented case among divine names registered for commercial use. == See Also == * {{ill|Haraedo-no-Ōkami|ja|祓戸大神|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Ōharae Kotoba|ja|大祓詞|12=draft|12=draft}}
